stylometry: We did a clustering analysis in our use of data mining.  First, we gathered data and entered it into a table.  Then we standardized the data, to avoid issues that arise from using the actual values.  We then found the squared distances to the centers (the variance.)  The square root of the variance is the standard deviation.  By knowing the standard deviation, we can appropriately cluster the data in an intelligent manner.  We follow this by determining the cluster centers.  We then assign each data point to the cluster that best suits it.
